g','CD',25,'Known also as the Trickster of Tzeentch, the Changeling can alter its form at will to mimic mortal beings from the smallest insect to the most titanic monster. The daemonâ€™s favourite game is to impersonate pivotal mortal leaders or heroes, and then to wreak untold mischief by abusing their power and position.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Infernal Flames; the Tricksterâ€™s Staff.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/chaos-daemons/The-Changeling'),(1119,'The Blue Scribes','CD',25,'These quarrelsome daemons flit through time and space upon their skimming Disc, seeking scattered shards of the sorcerous wisdom of Tzeentch. Pâ€™tarix leeches away the secrets and power of enemy sorcerers, even as Xiratâ€™p unleashes storms of sorcerous destruction drawn from their arcane stash of lore.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> sharp quills.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/chaos-daemons/The-Blue-Scribes'),(1120,'Lord of Change','CD',25,'Greater Daemons of Tzeentch are infinitely cunning sorcerers and manipulators. Their malevolent gaze lays bare the souls of their victims and blasts the sanity of even the staunchest mortal, while their ensorcelled weapons and unholy magicks violently reshape reality itself into ever mutating forms.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Bolt of Change; staff of Tzeentch.','','false','','','1-7','While this model has 1-7 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/chaos-daemons/Lord-of-Change'),(1125,'Flamers','CD',25,'These bizarre daemons bound through the air in convulsive leaps. The warpflame that drools from their many maws seethes with the raw power of change. When spat forth in roaring sheets, it sends its victims into agonies of mutation, their forms altering again and again before collapsing into distorted ruin.','Other','<b>Every mod