ttps://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Falchion'),(4109,'Lord of Poxes','DG',14,'The Lord of Poxes lumbers into battle amidst a churning cloud of spore-thick plague smog. These foul fumes wheeze from the miasmic turbine borne upon this monstrous championâ€™s shoulders and cannot only veil advancing Death Guard warriors from harm but also send foes crumpling to the ground as they claw at swollen throats and drown on their dissolving lungs.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> plasma pistol; great plague blade.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Lord-of-Poxes'),(4110,'Foetid Bloat-drone with Heavy Blight Launcher','DG',14,'Some Foetid Bloat-drones carry heavy blight launchers and the bulky ammo hoppers required to feed them. Thrumming ponderously into firing positions, these airborne monsters bombard the enemy with volleys of explosive shells. Each detonation unleashes swift-spreading blights that chew through flesh, rust metal and even corrode souls.','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> heavy blight launcher; plague probe.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Foetid-Bloat-drone-with-Heavy-Blight-Launcher'),(4111,'Rotigus','DG',14,'Rotigus Rainfather lumbers into battle, vomiting rivers of corrosive, plague-laden filth across all who stand in its path. In its bloated fist, it clutches a gnarlrod while an endless and infectious downpour accompanies the daemon, a fecund flood fit to drown, corrupt and mutate all it touches.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> streams of brackish filth; gnarlrod.','','false','','','1-7','While this model has 1-7 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Rotigus'),(4112,'Great Unclean One','DG',14,'These greater daemons possess the same boundless energy and drive to corrupt as a swift-spreading virus. Their booming voices roll across the battlefield, their cruel jollity and the perverse pride they take in their underlingsâ€™ achievements horribly at odds with the misery and disease they spread.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> plague flail; putrid vomit; bilesword.','','false','','','1-7','While this model has 1-7 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Great-Unclean-One'),(4113,'Plaguebearers','DG',14,'Born from the souls of those who die of Nurgleâ€™s Rot, Plaguebearers are the foot soldiers of the Plague God. They wield plagueswords that drip with infectious slime and are surrounded by the endless drone of counting as they pursue their hopeless and eternal task of tallying each new outbreak of their masterâ€™s many diseases.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> plaguesword.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Plaguebearers'),(4114,'Plague Drones','DG',14,'Plague Drones ride monstrous rot flies to war. These vile steeds scrabble and rip at their prey, impaling them on dripping proboscis orbiting off the heads of their victims. The finest stolen craniums are recovered and fashioned into filth-swollen projectiles - deathâ€™s heads - for the daemonic riders to hurl at their foes.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> deathâ€™s heads; foul mouthparts; plaguesword.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Plague-Drones'),(4115,'Beasts of Nurgle','DG',14,'Filled with dim-witted ebullience at odds with their diseased and nightmarish forms, Beasts of Nurgle heave themselves into battle like eager hounds. They are drawn instinctively to mortal playthings, whose desperate cries and frantic flight they mistake for participation, at least until their luckless new friends have twitched their last.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> putrid appendages.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Beasts-of-Nurgle'),(4116,'Nurglings','DG',14,'Nurglings are malicious plague mites that pour across the battlefield in giggling masses. These foul imps might seem almost amusing from a distance, yet the illusion is shattered as the Nurglings spill forth to engulf their screaming victims in a rancid avalanche of needle fangs, filthy talons and bloated flesh.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> diseased claws and teeth.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/death-guard/Nurglings'),(634,'Archon','DRU',31,'Archons lead their kabals in battle with a mixture of malevolent cunning, arrogant self-assuredness and breathtaking martial skill. To these qualities, they add an arsenal of esoteric weaponry and wargear that enable them to fight wreathed in concealing shadows, drag the souls from their victimsâ€™ bodies, and reduce enemies to desiccated ashes with a single blow.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> splinter pistol; huskblade; shadowfield.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Archon'),(639,'Succubus','DRU',31,'Succubi are the leaders of the wych cults and master combatants of the arena, their warrior artistry as ferociously savage as sublimely graceful. Disdaining heavy armour in favour of lithe agility, they hurl themselves into the teeth of the foe without fear, cutting a murderous path through all who oppose them and indelibly stamping their superiority upon the battle.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Archite glaive and agoniser.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Succubus'),(640,'Lelith Hesperax','DRU',31,'Lelith Hesperax is the undisputed queen of the Commorrite arenas, a warrior capable of felling the mightiest armoured foes and most monstrous beasts with a pair of simple - if beautifully balanced - knives. Hesperax makes a spectacle of her every battle, dancing and weaving around her victims with mocking ease as she builds to a spectacularly gory crescendo.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Lelithâ€™s blades.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Lelith-Hesperax'),(641,'Haemonculus','DRU',31,'Wielding horrific torture implements from their oubliettes and laboratories, Haemonculi drift like sinister predators through the midst of battle. They direct their covens of twisted monstrosities and pain adepts while hungrily seeking out fresh subjects for their hideous fleshcrafting, spreading terror through the foe with the detached fascination of true connoisseurs.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> stinger pistol; Haemonculus tools and scissorhands.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Haemonculus'),(642,'Urien Rakarth','DRU',384,'Urien Rakarth is the most ingenious of the many Haemonculi masters. He is the Sculptor of Torments, whose repugnant creations strain his enemiesâ€™ sanity. Once his casket of fanged spirits and his toxin-laced blades are finished, a coiling nest of Haemovores feast upon whatever is left of Rakarthâ€™s foes.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Casket of Flensing; Haemonculus tools and scissorhands.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Urien-Rakarth'),(643,'Drazhar','DRU',31,'Stalking the battlefields of realspace with a singular and murderous focus, Drazhar fights in utter silence. His bladework is phenomenal, his skill peerless. His only desire appears to be killing for killingâ€™s sake, for he hacks a bloody path through mighty champions and luckless dregs alike, reducing all to butchered corpses with the same contemptuous ease.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Executionerâ€™s demiklaives.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Drazhar'),(644,'Kabalite Warriors','DRU',31,'Only the best of a kabalâ€™s warriors are afforded a place within its raiding parties, and every one fights all the more savagely to prove their merit. Clad in barbed and segmented armour, wielding vicious splinter weaponry or potent armaments tailored to butcher infantry or annihilate enemy armour, they form the dark heart of many realspace raids.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> splinter rifle; close combat weapon.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Kabalite-Warriors'),(646,'Wyches','DRU',31,'Wyches are gladiatorial murder artists who exhibit their incredible skills to slay with precision and Ã©lan. Used to corralling wild beasts in the arenas, their assaults are so swift and overwhelming that enemies often find themselves encircled by Wyches who have weaved through or sprung over their ranks to trap them in a rapidly tightening noose of blades.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> splinter pistol; Hekatarii blade.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Wyches'),(648,'Incubi','DRU',31,'The Incubi are warrior perfectionists of the highest order. Protected by the ornate plates of their ancient warsuits, they move swiftly in for the kill, sweeping giant klaives in practised, decapitating strikes. They carve straight through the enemyâ€™s elite, crushing their spirit with psychic torture devices known as tormentors.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> klaive.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Incubi'),(649,'Mandrakes','DRU',31,'Creatures of midnight horror, crawling through the shadows to slither into the most secure locations, Mandrakes radiate an aura of frigid evil. They can conjure and hurl balefires at will to sear their victimsâ€™souls from the inside out, while any who face these ghoulish killers up close are soon hacked down by the blows of grossly outsized razors and vicious torture blades.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> baleblast; glimmersteel blade.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Mandrakes'),(650,'Wracks','DRU',31,'The gnarled hide of the Wracks is a leathery mass of old scars, inured to pain. These adepts of fleshcrafting serve the wizened masters of the covens and are as much experiments in stitch and sinew as apprentices to the Haemonculusâ€™ gruesome craft. They are granted a host of cruel tools, butchering blades and arcane bioweapons with which they inflict maximum agony.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> twin torturerâ€™s tools.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Wracks'),(651,'Grotesques','DRU',384,'These modified meat-hulks are pumped full of painful chemicals, growth elixirs and macro-steroids. With swollen muscles they hack their masterâ€™s foes apart, their brutal cleavers and grafted claws dripping with toxins. They are mindlessly obedient and insensible to any hurt, chasing down fleeing prey at the behest of their creator.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> paired monstrous weapons.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Grotesques'),(652,'Beastmaster','DRU',384,'On thrumming skyboards that spit venom-laced shards, Beastmasters hover above the frenzied bloodletting of their thrall-creatures, goading them on with the cruel lashes of a nerve-inflaming agoniser. Many wear shamanistic masks that augment the wearerâ€™s natural dominance with sub-vocal emissions and subjugating pheromones.','Characters','<b>The Beastmaster is equipped with:</b> splinter pods; agoniser. <br><br><b>Every Clawed Fiend is equipped with</b>: Clawed Fiend fists. <br><br><b>Every Khymerae is equipped with:</b> Khymerae talons. <br><br><b>Every Razorwing Flock is equipped with:</b> Razorwing feathers.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Beastmaster'),(656,'Raider','DRU',31,'These swift anti-grav transport barques are employed by kabals, wych cults and haemonculus covens alike for their realspace raids. Streaking through skies like poisoned arrows, Raiders deliver their cargoes of vicious Drukhari into the very heart of the foe before their victims have time to react, providing vicious covering fire as the fighting intensifies.','Dedicated Transports','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> dark lance; bladevanes and chainsnares.','This model has a transport capacity of 11 Drukhari Infantry models (excluding Jump Pack models).','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Raider'),(657,'Venom','DRU',31,'Raw speed delivers countless Venom transports to the heart of the enemyâ€™s defence and sees them chase down stragglers and encircle the foeâ€™s outriders. For the clique of warriors on board, Venoms are mobile firebases and gore-splashed chariots in one, with flickering shields that confound attempts to bring them down.','Dedicated Transports','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> splinter cannon; twin splinter rifle; bladevanes.','This model has a transport capacity of 6 Drukhari Infantry models (excluding Jump Pack models).<br><br>Before the battle, at the start of the Declare Battle Formations step, you can select one Kabalite Warriors, Hand of the Archon or Wyches unit from your army that has not already been split. If you do, that unit is split into two units, each containing as equal a number of models as possible (when splitting a unit in this way, make a note of which models form each of the two new units]. One of these units must start the battle embarked within this model; the other can start the battle embarked within another <span class=\"kwb\">TRANSPORT</span>, or it can be deployed as a separate unit.','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Venom'),(658,'Reavers','DRU',31,'Reaver jetbikes streak across the battlefield with the same speed and agility they display during their lethal races around the Commorrite arenas. Whether jinking around incoming enemy fire, decapitating foes with vicious bladevanes or culling their victims with ferocious firepower, these high-speed killers are lethal in the extreme.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> splinter pistol; splinter rifle; bladevanes.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Reavers'),(659,'Hellions','DRU',31,'When the Hellion gangs ride their bladed skyboards alongside Drukhari raiding parties, they bring terror to the battlefields of realspace. Arrogant and agile, Hellions wield their hellglaives with such skill that battle becomes a contest as to who amongst them can perform the most ostentatious acts of spectacular airborne slaughter.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> splinter pods; hellglaive.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Hellions'),(660,'Razorwing Jetfighter','DRU',31,'Though agile and capable air superiority craft, the true worth of Razorwing Jetfighters is in ground attack runs. Blurring low over the heads of the foe, they unleash salvoes of missiles whose specialised warheads sow bloody horror. Soon enough, the enemy are left cowering in disarray at the mere threat of another pass by the murderous Razorwings and their sadistic pilots.','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> 2 dark lances; Razorwing missiles; twin splinter rifle; bladed wings.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Razorwing-Jetfighter'),(661,'Voidraven Bomber','DRU',31,'Mounting some of the most powerful guns in the Drukhari arsenal, the Voidraven Bomberâ€™s dark scythes and void lances can crack heavily armoured targets. Yet they pale against the silent aircraftâ€™s primary weapon - the void mine. Once this arcane payload is deployed, the resulting darklight implosion erases all caught within its blast.','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> 2 void lances; bladed wings.','','false','','','1-4','While this model has 1-4 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Voidraven-Bomber'),(662,'Scourges with Heavy Weapons','DRU',31,'Airborne messengers and mercenaries who ride the thermals between Commorraghâ€™s highest spires, Scourges have been bodily modified for winged flight. They wear their grotesque new forms with the same pride that they wield their massive dark lances and splinter cannons, for their combination of speed and firepower renders them invaluable.','Other','<b>The Solarite is equipped with:</b> shardcarbine; close combat weapon.<br><br><b>Every Scourge is equipped with:</b> splinter cannon; close combat weapon.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Scourges-with-Heavy-Weapons'),(663,'Talos','DRU',31,'The Talos Pain Engine is a ghoulish melding of stitch-puckered flesh and armoured artifice, boasting tremendous resilience and a nightmarish array of weaponry. Each is the proud creation of the Drukhari Haemonculi, who employ their Talos as torture devices, surgical assistants and armoured murder machines.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> twin splinter cannon; 2 macro-scalpels.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Talos'),(664,'Cronos','DRU',31,'Like other Engines of Pain, the Cronos is a grisly amalgam of stimm-fed flesh and biomechanical implements shielded by a burnished carapace. Haemonculi create the Cronos to act as a parasite. Its esoteric syphons leech its victimâ€™s life essence, leaving them as husks before projecting the stolen vitality to other Drukhari.','Other','Every Cronos is equipped with: spirit syphon; spirit-leech tentacles.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Cronos'),(665,'Ravager','DRU',31,'Ravager gunships fulfil the role of armoured fire support during Drukhari raids, leveraging their speed and agility to outmanoeuvre the more heavily armoured war engines with which they typically duel. They are mobile assassins, mounting enough firepower to gut enemy tanks and eradicate the foeâ€™s elite warriors before swiftly relocating to new hunting grounds.','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> 3 dark lances; bladevanes.','','false','','','1-4','While this model has 1-4 wounds remaining, each time it makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Ravager'),(666,'Reaper','DRU',384,'','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> storm vortex projector; bladevanes; prow blade.','','false','','','1-4','While this model has 1-4 wounds remaining, each time it makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Reaper'),(667,'Tantalus','DRU',384,'The Tantalus is a prestigious twin-hulled Drukhari assault skimmer perfectly crafted for high-speed terror raids. The signature armament of the Tantalus is a set of graceful scythevanes that extend from the vehicleâ€™s hull, designed to slice and sever any foes caught in the skimmerâ€™s sweeping flight path.','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> pulse disintegrators; dire scythe blades.','This model has a transport capacity of 16 Drukhari Infantry models. Each Grotesque model takes up the space of 3 models. This model cannot transport models that can Fly.','false','','','1-6','While this model has 1-6 wounds remaining, each time it makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Tantalus'),(1390,'Raven Strike Fighter','DRU',384,'','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> 2 dark lances; splinterstorm cannon; Bladed wings.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/drukhari/Raven-Strike-Fighter'),(2471,'Court of the Archon','DRU',384,'Nothing but the manipulative cunning of an Archon could demand the loyalty of their varied Courts. Drawn from 