emaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Maulerfiend'),(4092,'Heldrake','EC',280,'','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Hades autocannon; Heldrake claws.','','false','','','1-4','While this model has 1-4 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Heldrake'),(4093,'Chaos Rhino','EC',280,'','Dedicated Transports','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> combi-bolter; armoured tracks.','This model has a transport capacity of 12 Emperorâ€™s Children Infantry models (excluding TERMiNATOR and Flawless Blade models).','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Chaos-Rhino'),(4094,'Shalaxi Helbane','EC',280,'Cloven hooves pounding against broken earth, Shalaxi Helbane bears down upon its doomed quarry with the Soulpiercer gleaming in its grip. No prey can evade the Monarch of the Hunt, for the daemonâ€™s obsession with its victim is so singular and so powerful that no mortal means of flight could ever escape it.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> lash of Slaanesh; Pavane of Slaanesh; snapping claws; Soulpiercer.','','false','','','1-7','While this model has 1-7 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Shalaxi-Helbane'),(4095,'Daemonettes','EC',280,'Known to mortals as the handmaidens of Slaanesh, these daemons are a mixture of the beautiful and the monstrous, made all the more disturbing by the visceral clash of both. They delight in the carnage of battle, weaving around enemiesâ€™ clumsy blows as they shrill and sigh their delight amidst swift-taloned slaughter.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> slashing claws.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Daemonettes'),(4096,'Fiends','EC',280,'Few daemonic entities approach the sheer disturbing horror of the Fiends of Slaanesh. Malicious hunting beasts that croon their delight across the battlefield, these ghastly abominations are wreathed in a soporific musk that leaves their prey witless and helpless before their flashing talons and stabbing tails.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> barbed tail and dissecting claws.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Fiends'),(4097,'Keeper of Secrets','EC',280,'Darkly intelligent, horribly beguiling and deadly in battle, the Keepers of Secrets are the greatest champions of Slaaneshi daemon legions. Wielding unclean yet beautiful weapons and unleashing the sorcerous powers of obsession and torment, these daemons cut an elegantly hideous swathe across the battlefield.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Phantasmagoria; snapping claws; witstealer sword.','','false','','','1-6','While this model has 1-6 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Keeper-of-Secrets'),(4098,'Seekers','EC',280,'Sat astride swift Steeds of Slaanesh, Seekers pursue their mortal prey with obsessive delight. Even the fastest of mortal vehicles cannot outpace these vicious entities, while those who stand and fight soon find their ranks smashed asunder by charging shock cavalry drawn from the darkest depths of nightmare.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> lashing tongue; slashing claws.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/emperor-s-children/Seekers'),(507,'Patriarch','GC',53,'Psychic abomination; alpha predator; parasitic demigod â€“ the Patriarch is all of these things and worse. They are the source of the bio corruption that spawns each Genestealer Cult cell. Moreover, when the Day of Ascension comes, they are the cultâ€™s deadliest killer, prowling the shadows of embattled worlds to rip and slay.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Patriarchâ€™s claws.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Patriarch'),(508,'Magus','GC',53,'The Magus acts as its Patriarchâ€™s vizier, and as the head of that alien monstrosityâ€™s deviant church. Each one is a powerful psyker, their formidable will enhanced by the gestalt powers of the Star Children until they can manipulate enemiesâ€™ minds and bodies like puppets â€“ or tear them apart from within.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; Magus stave.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Magus'),(509,'Primus','GC',53,'Occupying a role somewhere between guerrilla general and shadowy symbol of resistance, the Primus is a Genestealer Cultâ€™s ultimate military commander. Besides being deadly combatants in their own right, their mastery of insurgent tactics transforms their followers from a rebellious mob into a lethal military machine.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> scoped needle pistol; cult bonesword; toxin injector claw. ','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Primus'),(510,'Acolyte Iconward','GC',53,'It is a great honour to bear the cultâ€™s sigil aloft, out in the open for all to see. These banners are hung with pseudo-sacred artefacts, some stemming from the secretions or body of the Patriarch itself. The effect of the Acolyte Iconwardâ€™s presence upon nearby cult warriors is electrifying, driving them to new heights of violence.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; cult claws.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Acolyte-Iconward'),(511,'Acolyte Hybrids With Autopistols','GC',53,'Acolyte Hybrids comprise the earliest generations of a cultâ€™s brood cycles, and they are monstrous in body and mind. Some equip themselves with an array of automatic pistols and repurposed heavy tools, applying industrialised might to the battlefield in acts of sabotage or resource acquisition.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; cult claws and knife.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Acolyte-Hybrids-With-Autopistols'),(512,'Neophyte Hybrids','GC',53,'Making up the bulk of their cultâ€™s ranks, Neophyte Hybrids are the least alien in appearance of all the Patriarchâ€™s brood. They are no less dangerous for this, however, and what they lack in weaponised bio-adaptations they make up for in numbers, massed firepower and zealous revolutionary fanaticism.','Battleline','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; Hybrid firearm; close combat weapon.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Neophyte-Hybrids'),(513,'Hybrid Metamorphs','GC',53,'Triggered by the approach of a hive fleet or a sudden trauma to the cult, Hybrid Metamorphs mutate from early generations of the brood cycle. Dormant gene-codes burst to life, bestowing weaponised limbs, ghastly bio-acidic glands and other so-called blessings upon these creatures, transforming them into devastating shock troops.','Other','<b>The Metamorph Leader is equipped with:</b> autopistol; Leaderâ€™s bio-weapons.<br><br><b>Every Hybrid Metamorph is equipped with:</b> autopistol; Metamorph mutations.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Hybrid-Metamorphs'),(514,'Aberrants','GC',53,'No one truly knows what causes Aberrants to spring up amidst the brood cycle, yet the uses of these lumpen gene-deviants are obvious. Possessed of immense strength and resilience coupled with simplistic loyalty to the cult, they are hurled into battle as line breakers or massed as hulking, expendable bodyguards.','Other','<b>Every Aberrant is equipped with:</b> Aberrant weapons.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Aberrants'),(515,'Purestrain Genestealers','GC',53,'Vanguard organisms for the Tyranid hive fleets, Purestrain Genestealers are one of the most lethal life forms in the galaxy. They combine the cunning of an apex predator with inhuman speed and agility, closing with their prey in the blink of an eye before tearing their victims to bloody tatters.','Other','<b>Every model is equipped with:</b> cult claws and talons.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Purestrain-Genestealers'),(516,'Goliath Truck','GC',53,'Robust and versatile, the Goliath Truck is the armoured transport of choice for the Genestealer Cults. These vehicles boast thick armour and capacious holds, and their heavy stubber and twin autocannon allow the crew to lay down a hail of supporting fire as the broodkin passengers disembark into battle.','Dedicated Transports','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> heavy stubber; twin autocannon; demolition charge cache; armoured hull.','This model has a transport capacity of 12 Genestealer Cults Infantry models.','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Goliath-Truck'),(521,'Goliath Rockgrinder','GC',53,'The drilldozer blade fitted to the Goliath Rockgrinder is intended for gouging tunnels deep into solid rock faces in search of mineral riches. However, it works just as well as both an ablative shield and a hideously bloody line-breaking weapon, mangling a crimson path through the luckless foe.','Other','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> heavy mining laser; heavy stubber; drilldozer blade; demolition charge cache.','This model has a transport capacity of 6 Genestealer Cults Infantry models.','false','','','1-3','While this model has 1-3 wounds remaining, each time this model makes an attack, subtract 1 from the Hit roll.','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Goliath-Rockgrinder'),(1546,'Abominant','GC',53,'Born from the sting of a mindwyrm familiar, the Abominant is an Aberrant tainted with the Patriarchâ€™s own gene-mass. This transforms the beast into a mountain of mutated chitin and muscle that can regenerate as swiftly as its foes can harm it, and whose raw might is a lethal battlefield asset.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> power sledgehammer.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Abominant'),(1565,'Jackal Alphus','GC',53,'The Jackal Alphus rides their dirtcycle to commanding battlefield vantage points. With their long-range vox, the Alphus calls in strike missions against tougher, armoured targets. Should a foe fall beneath the cross hairs of their cult sniper rifle, its life expectancy can be measured in moments.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; cult sniper rifle; close combat weapon.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Jackal-Alphus'),(1567,'Clamavus','GC',53,'Vox-hacker and information assassin supreme, the Clamavus scythes into enemy communications networks for intelligence. It seeds the amplified psychic signal of the Broodmind through the foeâ€™s comms to spread dismay from a distance, while up close it can rupture its victimsâ€™ brains with its savage audial symphony.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; close combat weapon.','','false','','<i>You can attach this model to a <span class=\"kwb\">ACOLYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> or <span class=\"kwb\">NEOPHYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> unit, even if a Primus, Magus or Acolyte Iconward model has already been attached to it. If you do, and that Bodyguard unit is destroyed, the Leader units attached to it become separate units, with their original Starting Strengths.</i>','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Clamavus'),(1568,'Locus','GC',53,'An unassuming bodyguard, the Locus may be overlooked by the foe until the exact moment it abandons calm stillness for lightning-fast attack. Robes thrown back, the Locusâ€™ whipping tail barb and vestigial limbs are revealed even as its twin blades flash out to neutralise any threats to its ward.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Locus blades. ','','false','','<i>You can attach this model to a <span class=\"kwb\">ACOLYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> or <span class=\"kwb\">NEOPHYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> unit, even if a Primus, Magus or Acolyte Iconward model has already been attached to it. If you do, and that Bodyguard unit is destroyed, the Leader units attached to it become separate units, with their original Starting Strengths.</i>','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Locus'),(1569,'Sanctus','GC',53,'A Sanctus is an inescapable assassin who can track by psychic spoor and squirm through the smallest gaps. Its bio-dagger â€“ spawned from the Patriarchâ€™s genesis pools â€“ unleashes the psychic might of the Broodmind with the slightest cut, while the Sanctusâ€™ cult sniper rifle allows it to strike down prey from afar.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> Sanctus bio-dagger.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Sanctus'),(1570,'Kelermorph','GC',53,'This gunfighter is a living icon of rebellion, moulded to exploit the psyche of fractured Human societies. Whip-fast reactions and hypersensory acuity lend the Kelermorph lethal reaction speeds and help it unleash withering volleys from its iconic liberator autostubs, whose depleted volonium rounds can punch through tank armour.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> liberator autostubs; close combat weapon.','','false','','','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Kelermorph'),(1571,'Nexos','GC',53,'Engineered to share a portion of the Patriarchâ€™s cerebral might, the Nexos can absorb the entirety of a cultistâ€™s thoughts and experiences through physical contact. They compartmentalise millions of these snapshots, building a formidable mental map, then using it to direct cult forces like a rear-echelon officer of prodigious skill.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; close combat weapon.','','false','','<i>You can attach this model to a <span class=\"kwb\">ACOLYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> or <span class=\"kwb\">NEOPHYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> unit, even if a Primus, Magus or Acolyte Iconward model has already been attached to it. If you do, and that Bodyguard unit is destroyed, the Leader units attached to it become separate units, with their original Starting Strengths.</i>','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Nexos'),(1572,'Biophagus','GC',53,'The Biophagus is a scientist-surgeon whose injector goad can be used to enhance the unholy might of Aberrants and other favoured cultists, or to dose enemies with a mutagenic cocktail that rapidly dissolves them from within. Coupled with hurled vials of bio-acids, this arsenal renders the Biophagus a deadly agent of biological warfare.','Characters','<b>This model is equipped with:</b> autopistol; chemical vials; injector goad, alchemicus familiar.','','false','','<i>You can attach this model to a <span class=\"kwb\">ACOLYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> or <span class=\"kwb\">NEOPHYTE</span> <span class=\"kwb\">HYBRIDS</span> unit, even if a Primus, Magus or Acolyte Iconward model has already been attached to it. If you do, and that Bodyguard unit is destroyed, the Leader units attached to it become separate units, with their original Starting Strengths.</i>','','','https://wahapedia.ru/wh40k10ed/factions/genestealer-cults/Biophagus'),(1573,'Achilles Ridgerunners','GC',53,'The operators of these lightweight but rugged scout vehicles help to coordinate lethal armoured ambushes that eliminate isolated foes or se